        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD took them to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4481.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">James de Carle Sowerby</ref>, who drew the figures of the fossil Lepadidae. See <ref target="./DCP-LETT-1303.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to James de Carle Sowerby, 12 February [1850]</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Of Fitch’s specimens, CD described five species (two of <hi rend="italic">Scalpellum</hi> and three of <hi rend="italic">Pollicipes</hi>), besides several varieties of <hi rend="italic">Scalpellum maximum</hi>, all from the Upper Chalk of Norwich.</note>
        </div>        
            
